The Biden-Harris Administration has announced the leadership team for the newly-established CHIPS for America offices, which will be responsible for implementing the CHIPS and Science Act's $50 billion investment in the semiconductor industry. Ronnie Chatterji will serve as the White House Coordinator for CHIPS Implementation, while Michael Schmidt will be the Director of the CHIPS Program Office at the Department of Commerce. Eric Lin will serve as the Interim Director of the CHIPS Research and Development Office, and Todd Fisher will be the Interim Senior Advisor in the CHIPS Program Office. Donna Dubinsky and J.D. Grom will also serve as Senior Counselor and Senior Advisor, respectively, in the Office of the Secretary. These leaders bring extensive experience in government, industry, and large-scale program management to their roles. Their work will focus on bolstering supply chains, driving research investments, enhancing national security, and creating jobs.